\pard\sa160\sl259\slmult0\f0\fs32\lang9 Q 1 Explain the difference between inline ,internal,and external css.\par

\pard\sb100\sa100\sl240\slmult1\b\f1 Answer.\fs27  1. Inline CSS (\lang1033 CSS)\par
\fs24\lang9 Definition:\b0  CSS styles are written \b directly in the HTML tag\b0  using the \f2\fs20 style\f1\fs24  attribute.\par
 \b Use Case:\b0  When you want to apply a unique style to a \b single element only\b0 .\par
\b Example:\b0\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\tx916\tx1832\tx2748\tx3664\tx4580\tx5496\tx6412\tx7328\tx8244\tx9160\tx10076\tx10992\tx11908\tx12824\tx13740\tx14656\b\f2\fs20 html\par
<p style="color: red; font-size: 20px;">This is inline CSS</p>\par
\par

\pard\sb100\sa100\sl240\slmult1\f1\fs27 2. Internal CSS (\lang1033 CSS)\par
\fs24\lang9 Definition:\b0  CSS is written \b inside a \f2\fs20 <style>\f1\fs24  tag\b0  within the \f2\fs20 <head>\f1\fs24  section of the HTML document.\par
\f3 .\b\f1 Use Case:\b0  When you want to apply styles to a \b single HTML page only\b0 .\par
 \b Example:\b0\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\tx916\tx1832\tx2748\tx3664\tx4580\tx5496\tx6412\tx7328\tx8244\tx9160\tx10076\tx10992\tx11908\tx12824\tx13740\tx14656\b\f2\fs20 html\par
CopyEdit\par
<html>\par
<head>\par
  <style>\par
    p \{\par
      color: blue;\par
      font-size: 18px;\par
    \}\par
  </style>\par
</head>\par
<body>\par
  <p>This is internal CSS</p>\par
</body>\par
</html>\par
\par
\par

\pard\sb100\sa100\sl240\slmult1\f1\fs27 3. External CSS (\lang1033 CSS)\par
\fs24\lang9 Definition:\b0  CSS is written in a \b separate \f2\fs20 .css\f1\fs24  file\b0  and linked to the HTML using the \f2\fs20 <link>\f1\fs24  tag.\par
\f3\lang1033 *\f4\lang9  \b\f1 Use Case:\b0  Best for \b large websites\b0  with multiple pages.\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\tx916\tx1832\tx2748\tx3664\tx4580\tx5496\tx6412\tx7328\tx8244\tx9160\tx10076\tx10992\tx11908\tx12824\tx13740\tx14656\f2\fs20 html\par
\b\par
<!-- HTML file -->\par
<head>\par
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">\par
</head>\par
<body>\par
  <p>This is external CSS</p>\par
</body>\par
css\par
