Q3.Discuss the CSS box model and its \b0\fs32 components\b\fs36 .\par
Answer:\par
\par
The \b0 CSS Box Model is a fundamental concept in web development. It describes how each HTML element is represented as a rectangular box and how its size and spacing are calculated.\par
\par
\par
---\par
\par
Components of the CSS Box Model:\par
\par
1). Content:\par
The area where text or images appear. Size is set using width and height.\par
\par
\par
2). Padding:\par
The space between the content and the border. It adds space inside the element.\par
\par
\par
3). Border:\par
A line around the padding and content. Its size and style can be customized.\par
\par
\par
4). Margin:\par
The space outside the border. It separates the element from others.\par
\par
\f3 .\f0  Box Model Diagram:\par
\par
+---------------------------+\par
|         Margin            |\par
|  +---------------------+  |\par
|  |       Border        |  |\par
|  |  +---------------+  |  |\par
|  |  |    Padding    |  |  |\par
|  |  | +-----------+ |  |  |\par
|  |  | |  Content  | |  |  |\par
|  |  | +-----------+ |  |  |\par
|  |  +---------------+  |  |\par
|  +---------------------+  |\par
+---------------------------+\par
\par
\par
\par
\par
* Example CSS Code:\par
\par
div \{\par
  width: 200px;\par
  padding: 20px;\par
  border: 5px solid black;\par
  margin: 10px;\par
\}\par
\par
This code creates a box with:\par
\par
Content width: 200px\par
\par
Padding: 20px\par
\par
Border: 5px\par
\par
Margin: 10px\par
\par
\par
Total width = 200 + 40 (padding) + 10 (border) = 250px (excluding margin)\par

